{"uid":"790267bec0073565","name":"QA 1922","fullName":"QA #1922 on centos-stream8-container","historyId":"1922@centos-stream8-container","time":{"start":1784756967000,"stop":1784756968000,"duration":1000},"description":"PCP QA Test No. 1922\n\nExercise pmproxy REST API /series/values endpoint with negative\n\nrelative time offsets (e.g. start=-30s).  This is the end-to-end\n\nintegration test for the series/values time parsing fix\n\n(GitHub issue #2503).\n\n\n\nWithout the fix, pmproxy crashes or disconnects when it receives\n\na negative relative offset.  With the fix, it returns an empty\n\narray (the archive data is from 2017, so -30s finds nothing).\n\n\n\nCopyright (c) 2024 Red Hat.\n\n\n\n","descriptionHtml":"<p>PCP QA Test No. 1922</p>\n<p>Exercise pmproxy REST API /series/values endpoint with negative</p>\n<p>relative time offsets (e.g. start=-30s).  This is the end-to-end</p>\n<p>integration test for the series/values time parsing fix</p>\n<p>(GitHub issue #2503).</p>\n<p>Without the fix, pmproxy crashes or disconnects when it receives</p>\n<p>a negative relative offset.  With the fix, it returns an empty</p>\n<p>array (the archive data is from 2017, so -30s finds nothing).</p>\n<p>Copyright (c) 2024 Red Hat.</p>\n","status":"passed","statusMessage":"","flaky":false,"newFailed":false,"newBroken":false,"newPassed":false,"retriesCount":0,"retriesStatusChange":false,"beforeStages":[],"afterStages":[],"labels":[{"name":"suite","value":"centos-stream8-container"},{"name":"host","value":"centos-stream8-container"},{"name":"epic","value":"pmseries"},{"name":"epic","value":"pmproxy"},{"name":"epic","value":"libpcp_web"},{"name":"epic","value":"local"},{"name":"resultFormat","value":"allure2"}],"parameters":[],"links":[{"name":"Source","url":"https://github.com/performancecopilot/pcp/tree/9a9be68f2b1404e43659ce54fa769b4a30f0739b/qa/1922","type":"test_case"},{"name":"Expected output","url":"https://github.com/performancecopilot/pcp/tree/9a9be68f2b1404e43659ce54fa769